getCurrentWrapper

public AeProcessWrapper getCurrentWrapper(long aProcessId)
Description copied from interface: IAeProcessWrapperMap
Returns the current process wrapper for the given process id or null if there is no process wrapper for the given process id. Does not increment the wrapper's reference count the way IAeProcessWrapperMap.getWrapper(long) does, so does not require a matching call to IAeProcessWrapperMap.releaseWrapper(AeProcessWrapper). However, this means that successive calls to IAeProcessWrapperMap.getCurrentWrapper(long) with the same process id may return different process wrappers.

Specified by:
getCurrentWrapper in interface IAeProcessWrapperMap

getWrapper

public AeProcessWrapper getWrapper()
Description copied from interface: IAeProcessWrapperMap
Returns an empty process wrapper. It manufactures a unique id for the map. This call should be followed by a call to set the process id. Each call to IAeProcessWrapperMap.getWrapper() or IAeProcessWrapperMap.getWrapper(long) must be followed eventually by a matching call to IAeProcessWrapperMap.releaseWrapper(AeProcessWrapper).

Specified by:
getWrapper in interface IAeProcessWrapperMap
See Also:
IAeProcessWrapperMap.getWrapper()

getWrapper

public AeProcessWrapper getWrapper(long aProcessId)
Description copied from interface: IAeProcessWrapperMap
Returns process wrapper for the specified process id. Adds a process wrapper for the process if one does not yet exist. Each call to IAeProcessWrapperMap.getWrapper(long) must be followed eventually by a matching call to IAeProcessWrapperMap.releaseWrapper(AeProcessWrapper).
